Adding @ConfigurationProperties("sfg.brewery") prefix to propertied defiend in the application.properties file
@ConfigurationProperties works best with hierarchical properties that all have the same prefix.
The Spring framework uses standard Java bean setters, so we must declare setters for each of the properties.

using RestTemplateBuilder
Best practice is to use create RestTemplateBuilder and then build RestTemplate from it. RestTemplateBuilder allows us to configure
different properties such as security.

we use constructo base injection to build restTemplateBuilder. Spring will inject RestTemplateBuilder thru the constructor
private RestTemplate restTemplate;
public ClassName(RestTemplateBuilder restTemplateBuilder) {
    restTemplate = restTemplateBuilder.build();
}
